HEADWORD: -esque
<hw>-esque</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F., fr. It. <ets>-isco</ets>. Cf.
<er>-ish</er>.]</ety> <def>A suffix of certain words from the French,
Italian, and Spanish. It denotes <xex>manner</xex> or <xex>style</xex>;
<xex>like</xex>; <as>as, arab<ex>esque</ex>, after the manner of the
Arabs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

